of her choice.  The Government noted that Ms. B.K. was brought to Panchkhal Barracks on 17
February 2004 at 8.30. The Colonel ordered two Captains to interrogate her.  She was questioned
and according to the Government she died at 11:30am due to &#8216;wrong methods&#8217;. The General
Martial Court found the three officers guilty. The two officials who had interrogated her were
sentenced to six months imprisonment. The Colonel was ordered to pay 50,000 rupees and each
